The Odewale ruling house of Alausa in Ikeja local government has announced Alhaji Muftau Beedmos as the Baale-elect of Alausa town. Alhaji Muftau Beedmos was announced the baale-elect after a crucial meeting for the selection of a new baale by the Odewale ruling house. In a statement forwarded to the Ministry of local Government and community affairs, the Odewale ruling house agreed unanimously to the selection of Alhaji Muftau Beedmos as the rightful person to occupy the baaleship stool which has long been vacant and unoccupied. The ruling house however stressed that it would keep the public abreast of the development and other formal rites.